<div class="page">
  <div class="page-header">
    <span>§ 04 — Cold Call Framework</span>
    <span class="right">Renterra BDR · Chris Khoury</span>
  </div>

  <div class="eyebrow">The script behind the talk track</div>
  <h1>Five moves that earn the next conversation.</h1>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 6.5in; margin-bottom: 0.2in;">
    A 5–10 minute discovery call has one job: get them talking about how they run today,
    surface one or two real pain points, and earn 20 minutes with an AE. Pitch features and
    you lose. Ask questions and listen, and you win.
  </p>

  <div class="flow-step">
    <div class="flow-num">1</div>
    <div class="flow-content">
      <h4>Opener — Permission &amp; pattern interrupt (15–30 sec)</h4>
      <p>Name the cold call. Ask for 30 seconds. Earn the right to keep talking. Blue-collar phone culture rewards directness — corporate scripts get hung up on inside 5 seconds.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="wedge" style="margin-top: -0.05in; margin-bottom: 0.15in;">
    <div class="lab">Script</div>
    <div class="quote">Hey [Name], this is Chris from Renterra — appreciate you picking up. I'll be honest, this is a cold call. Mind if I take 30 seconds to tell you why I'm calling, and then you can tell me to get lost or keep going?</div>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-step">
    <div class="flow-num">2</div>
    <div class="flow-content">
      <h4>Observation — Specific research callout</h4>
      <p>Show I've done the work. Mention something concrete about <em>their</em> business — fleet, locations, services. Generic openers ("hope you're having a great day") signal a bad list.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-step">
    <div class="flow-num">3</div>
    <div class="flow-content">
      <h4>Problem question — Ask, then shut up</h4>
      <p>One open-ended question rooted in <em>their</em> business model. Then silence. The first person to speak after a good discovery question loses leverage. Take notes Jimmy can hear me writing — "Got it, let me write that down" signals real listening.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-step">
    <div class="flow-num">4</div>
    <div class="flow-content">
      <h4>Value bridge — Map Renterra to the pain they confirmed</h4>
      <p>Mirror the pain back in their words, then anchor to <em>one</em> specific Renterra capability — not the full feature list. See the mapping table below for the trigger-to-anchor moves.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flow-step">
    <div class="flow-num">5</div>
    <div class="flow-content">
      <h4>Close — Ask for 20 minutes, not a sale</h4>
      <p>Two concrete time slots ready. "Fair?" closes for a yes/no without being pushy. Don't ask for a sale on a cold call — ask for the next conversation with an AE.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="wedge" style="margin-top: -0.05in;">
    <div class="lab">Close Script</div>
    <div class="quote">Look, I'm not going to try to sell you anything on this call. What I'd love to do is set up 20 minutes — either later this week or next — where an AE can actually show you what this looks like running for a shop like yours. If after 20 minutes it's not for you, no harm done. Fair?</div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span>Renterra Mock Exercise · Chris Khoury</span>
    <span>08</span>
  </div>
</div>

