<div class="page">
  <div class="page-header">
    <span>§ 06 — Execution Plan</span>
    <span class="right">Day-of the mock</span>
  </div>

  <div class="eyebrow">Game day</div>
  <h1>Hillview Equipment — full mock-call run-of-show.</h1>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 6.5in; margin-bottom: 0.2in;">
    I'd lead with Hillview because it's the cleanest fit: heavy-equipment-first, contractor-oriented,
    service- and transport-heavy, asset-intensive. The hypothesis writes itself.
  </p>

  <div class="wedge" style="margin-bottom: 0.25in;">
    <div class="lab">Cold open for the mock</div>
    <div class="quote">I noticed Hillview rents, sells, transports, and services heavy equipment across New England. Usually at that point, the hard part is keeping machine availability, inspection condition, transport timing, and service status aligned. How are you managing that today?</div>
  </div>

  <h4>What I'm listening for</h4>
  <ul class="checklist" style="margin-bottom: 0.2in;">
    <li><strong>Manual availability checks</strong> across people or branches</li>
    <li><strong>Inspection photos</strong> stored outside the rental workflow (someone's iPhone, a shared drive)</li>
    <li><strong>Delivery and transport</strong> coordinated by texts or a whiteboard</li>
    <li><strong>Quote follow-up</strong> owned by memory instead of system tasks</li>
    <li><strong>Service status</strong> not visible to counter or sales teams</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="do-dont">
    <div class="col do">
      <h4>Do</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the prospect's name once early, once at the close — not more</li>
        <li>Match their energy and pace — owner-operators talk faster and shorter than corporate buyers</li>
        <li>Smile while talking — it audibly changes tone</li>
        <li>Let silence breathe after a discovery question</li>
        <li>Take notes the prospect can hear — "Let me write that down"</li>
        <li>Say "I'd rather not BS you" if I get stuck — honest beats faking it</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col dont">
      <h4>Don't</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Pitch features in the first 90 seconds — earn the right with a question</li>
        <li>Use corporate jargon: "platform," "solution," "leverage," "synergies"</li>
        <li>Fill silence — they will talk if I let them</li>
        <li>Promise pricing — anchor to the AE call</li>
        <li>Argue with objections — acknowledge first, then redirect</li>
        <li>End without a clear next step or a specific time slot</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4>Day-of checklist</h4>
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>This briefing open + Hillview page bookmarked</li>
    <li>Blank notepad and pen — physical, not screen, to avoid clicking sounds</li>
    <li>Quiet room with hardline or strong cell signal — bad audio kills credibility instantly</li>
    <li>Water nearby — voice cracks happen even on 5-min calls</li>
    <li>Two specific time slots ready for the close ("Thursday at 10, or Friday at 2 — what works?")</li>
  </ul>

